00>(9/20/00 10:28:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Wizard Uber Weapon Theory...</span><hr size=1> even though i don't play anymore, i still read alot of EQ related msgboards and websites. here's what i think about the wizard uber weapon quest.<br>
<br>
looking at the uber item pictures, i think the wizard quest item is the 'fire in the hand'. i had an idea like this a long time ago that i posted on the official eq msg board. i posted that wiz uber item should look like a fire in the hand with smoke coming out of it like those held torches. i also posted that necro's should get a scepter that glows and magicians get a rod with an orb on the end that changes colors.<br>
anyways,<br>
<br>
Quest seems to start at Solusek Ro, a new guy Solomen asks you to deliver a note to Camin Rah in Eurudin Library. here's what the note says:<br>
--------------------<br>
&quot;Hello, old friend, I have made an updated list and locations of the items required for my research.<br>
<br>
Dragon bones- Plane of Fear<br>
Jet Black egg- Unknown<br>
Mistletoe Powder- Old Sebilis<br>
Rune of Lost Thought- Unknown<br>
<br>
Contact me when you find them<br>
Solomen&quot;<br>
--------------------<br>
<br>
BREAKDOWN:<br>
<br>
Camin Rah - where the hell is he? i personally haven't looked but a lot of people say that he is not in Erudin. some people say they saw him in Dagnors, HighHold, and someone even said that a GM told him that Camin is a rare spawn, or despawns in 20mins after the servers go up or when someone gives him the note. I think maybe Camin walks around the erudin librabry and his path collides with a wall or something making him stuck outside the database (similar to the jboots problem), or maybe he is invisible, or maybe he is a triggered spawn, or maybe when you talk to someone they will turn into Camin (like the sky quest npc's), or maybe verant just haven't put the damn NPC in the game yet; only time will tell where the hell he is.<br>
<br>
Dragon bones - Plane of Fear<br>
-only dragon in fear is draco, so i guess draco drops this every now and then.<br>
<br>
Jet Black Egg - Unknown<br>
-sounds like a sky item to me, otherwise.. hmm.. rare drop from a new rare named snake somewhere?<br>
<br>
Mistletoe Powder - Old Sebilis<br>
-maybe a named mushroom drops this? never been that far down in sebilis.<br>
<br>
Rune of lost thought - Unknown<br>
-no idea, probably a semi rare drop from a big gun, like venril or one of the kunark dragons<br>
<br>
THEORY:<br>
Look at the fiery avenger quest and use that as a reference to these new quests. the fiery avenger quest consists of:<br>
<br>
-2 dragon(god) loot (vox/nagafen book)<br>
-1 semi-hard to get loot (soulfire)<br>
-1 rare drop from a mid level frog (Ghoulbane)<br>
-killing a semi hard mob (miragu)<br>
-getting to a certain spot of zone &lt;4th island in sky(or is it 5th island?)&gt;<br>
<br>
so compare that to the info we have about the wizard item:<br>
<br>
-DRAGON BONES (i would consider this a dragon/god loot, it rivals nagafen and vox)<br>
-MISTLETOE POWDER (i don't exactly know where this drop, but this CAN be the 'ghoulbane' of our quest}<br>
-JET BLACK EGG (who knows where this damn thing drops, perhaps this will be the 'soulfire' of our quest?)<br>
-RUNE OF LOST THOUGHT (sounds like a dragon/god loot to me, maybe this will be the 2nd dragon loot of the quest)<br>
<br>
CONCLUSION:<br>
we don't really know how easy this quest will be until we get some sort of confirmation on where the some of the items are found or if this is just small part of the big quest for the wiz uber item. i just hope that we don't need to go in VP or wait for the Velious expansion to finish the quest. =)<br>
<br>
post whatever info you find here.<br>
<br>
